{
  "name": "Blood Money Pot*",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A decorated small earthen pot that is clearly very old. The design is of various lines of different thickness, yet none of the lines appear in a 45 degree or multiple of 45 degree angle. It holds a dully glimmering deep crimson paste which smells intensely of iron. Investigation reveals it to be blood mixed with powdered gemstones. The pot itself weights roughly 2 pounds.</p><ul><li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a spell has a component cost that consumes the component, its caster can substitute the required component for an amount of the paste found inside of an equal value.</span></li><li>You can substitute the paste for the material cost when transcribing spells into a spellbook and creating spell scrolls.</li></ul><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Every ~500gp worth is 1 lbs.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em>Perhaps the secret to creating more of this hidden amongst the drawings on this pot.</em></span></p><section id=\"secret-G4teojj8vyCH63sj\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Tracking the remaining amount of paste that remains in the pot is up to the user, you can edit this description to track it if you wish.</p></section>",
      "chat": ""
    },
